  "text": "The other steps in PP remain the same. Briefly, security in PP GV and CL GV arises as follows. The reordering has the same effect as time control and time randomization in GV. Eve is unable to apply a 2-qubit operation on legitimate partner particles to determine the encoding in spite of their orthogonality. Any correlation she generates by interacting with individual particles will diminish the observed correlations between Alice and Bob because of restrictions on shareability of quantum correlations [CITATION_1] . It is not our purpose to discuss the security of the protocol in detail here. Interested readers may found detailed discussions on the security of PP GV in Refs. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The PP GV protocol of Yadav, Srikanth and Pathak was the first ever orthogonal-state-based protocol of QSDC.",
